      • barSpacing

        Space between each bar, in pixels.

      • colorMap$array

        @Option(value="colorMap")
public String[] colorMap$array
        An array of values to specify a color for each individual bar. For example if your chart has three values 1,3,1 you can set colorMap$array=["red", "green", "blue"]

      • colorMap$map

        @Option(value="colorMap")
public Map<String,String> colorMap$map
        A range map to map specific values to selected colors. For example if you want all values of -2 to appear yellow, set colorMap: { '-2': '#ff0' }.

      • negBarColor

        @Option
public String negBarColor
        CSS color used for negative values.

      • nullColor

        @Option
public String nullColor
        CSS color used for values equal to null. By default null values are omitted entirely, but setting this adds a thin marker for the entry - This can be useful if your chart is pretty sparse; perhaps try setting it to a light grey or something equally unobtrusive.

      • stackedBarColor

        @Option
public String[] stackedBarColor
        An array of colors to use for stacked bar charts. The first series will use the first value in the array, the second series will use the second, etc.

      • zeroAxis

        @Option
public Boolean zeroAxis
        Centers the y-axis at zero if true.

        Default: true

      • zeroColor

        @Option
public String zeroColor
        CSS color used for values equal to zero.
